<div class="c220_17"> 
<div id="v220.17.1"><span class="H7307 s">My breath</span><span class="H2254 s"> is corrupt</span><span class="H3117 s">, my days</span><span class="H2193 s"> are extinct</span><span class="H6913 s">, the graves</span> <i>are ready</i> for me. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (breath…: or, spirit is spent)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.17.2"><span class="H2049 s"><i>Are there</i> not mockers</span><span class="H5869 s"> with me? and doth not mine eye</span><span class="H3885 s"> continue</span><span class="H4784 s"> in their provocation</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (continue: Heb. lodge)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.17.3"><span class="H7760 s">Lay down</span><span class="H6148 s"> now, put me in a surety</span><span class="H8628 s"> with thee; who <i>is</i> he <i>that</i> will strike</span><span class="H3027 s"> hands</span> with me?</div> 
<div id="v220.17.4"><span class="H6845 s">For thou hast hid</span><span class="H3820 s"> their heart</span><span class="H7922 s"> from understanding</span><span class="H7311 s">: therefore shalt thou not exalt</span> <i>them</i>.</div> 
<div id="v220.17.5"><span class="H5046 s">He that speaketh</span><span class="H2506 s"> flattery</span><span class="H7453 s"> to <i>his</i> friends</span><span class="H5869 s">, even the eyes</span><span class="H1121 s"> of his children</span><span class="H3615 s"> shall fail</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.17.6"><span class="H3322 s">He hath made</span><span class="H4914 s"> me also a byword</span><span class="H5971 s"> of the people</span><span class="H6440 s">; and aforetime</span><span class="H8611 s"> I was as a tabret</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (aforetime: or, before them)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.17.7"><span class="H5869 s">Mine eye</span><span class="H3543 s"> also is dim</span><span class="H3708 s"> by reason of sorrow</span><span class="H3338 s">, and all my members</span><span class="H6738 s"> <i>are</i> as a shadow</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (my members: or, my thoughts)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.17.8"><span class="H3477 s">Upright</span><span class="H8074 s"> <i>men</i> shall be astonied</span><span class="H5355 s"> at this, and the innocent</span><span class="H5782 s"> shall stir up</span><span class="H2611 s"> himself against the hypocrite</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.17.9"><span class="H6662 s">The righteous</span><span class="H270 s"> also shall hold</span><span class="H1870 s"> on his way</span><span class="H2890 s">, and he that hath clean</span><span class="H3027 s"> hands</span><span class="H3254 s"> shall be</span><span class="H555 s"> stronger and stronger</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (be…: Heb. add strength)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.17.10"><span class="H199 s">But</span><span class="H7725 s"> as for you all, do ye return</span><span class="H935 s">, and come now</span><span class="H4672 s">: for I cannot find</span><span class="H2450 s"> <i>one</i> wise</span> <i>man</i> among you.</div> 
<div id="v220.17.11"><span class="H3117 s">My days</span><span class="H5674 s"> are past</span><span class="H2154 s">, my purposes</span><span class="H5423 s"> are broken off</span><span class="H4180 s">, <i>even</i> the thoughts</span><span class="H3824 s"> of my heart</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the thoughts: Heb. the possessions)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.17.12"><span class="H7760 s">They change</span><span class="H3915 s"> the night</span><span class="H3117 s"> into day</span><span class="H216 s">: the light</span><span class="H7138 s"> <i>is</i> short</span><span class="H6440 s"> because</span><span class="H2822 s"> of darkness</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (short: Heb. near)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.17.13"><span class="H6960 s">If I wait</span><span class="H7585 s">, the grave</span><span class="H1004 s"> <i>is</i> mine house</span><span class="H7502 s">: I have made</span><span class="H3326 s"> my bed</span><span class="H2822 s"> in the darkness</span>.</div> 
<div id="v220.17.14"><span class="H7121 s">I have said</span><span class="H7845 s"> to corruption</span><span class="H1 s">, Thou <i>art</i> my father</span><span class="H7415 s">: to the worm</span><span class="H517 s">, <i>Thou art</i> my mother</span><span class="H269 s">, and my sister</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (said: Heb. cried, or, called)</span></div> 
<div id="v220.17.15"><span class="H645 s">And where <i>is</i> now</span><span class="H8615 s"> my hope</span><span class="H8615 s">? as for my hope</span><span class="H7789 s">, who shall see</span> it?</div> 
<div id="v220.17.16"><span class="H3381 s">They shall go down</span><span class="H905 s"> to the bars</span><span class="H7585 s"> of the pit</span><span class="H5183 s">, when <i>our</i> rest</span><span class="H3162 s"> together</span><span class="H6083 s"> <i>is</i> in the dust</span>.</div></div> 
